\f2\b\fs48 \cf2 \cb3 5) Interactivity (tiny, no-framework behaviors)\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 The 
\f2\b Interactivity API
\f1\b0  lets you add light client behavior to blocks without rolling your own framework. Great for toggles, tabs, and small UI touches. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.wordpress.org/block-editor/reference-guides/interactivity-api"}}{\fldrslt \cb3 \ul WordPress Developer Resources}}\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 HTML (in a pattern or template):
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs20\fsmilli10240 \cf6 \cb7 <div data-wp-interactive data-wp-context='\{"open": false\}'>\
  <button data-wp-on--click="actions.toggle">Menu</button>\
  <nav data-wp-bind--hidden="!state.open">\'85</nav>\
</div>\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 JS (enqueue once in your theme):
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs20\fsmilli10240 \cf6 \cb7 import \{ store \} from '@wordpress/interactivity';\
\
store('my-theme', \{\
  state: \{ open: false \},\
  actions: \{\
    toggle: (\{ state \}) => \{ state.open = !state.open; \}\
  \}\
\});\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Docs + directives reference here. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.wordpress.org/block-editor/reference-guides/interactivity-api/api-reference"}}{\fldrslt \cb3 \ul WordPress Developer Resources}}\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
